main event: Various orange-colored objects were observed in the sky near Wake Island on November 27, 1966.
interesting points: The objects had characteristics of a missile firing, but there was insufficient information to make an accurate analysis.

Aircrew interviews provided additional details, with one crew reporting a bright light that may have been an explosion, and another crew observing a bright object that left a yellow trail, appeared to climb, then explode with a green secondary explosion.
The phenomenon lit up the sky brightly for about 15 seconds.
The tracked origin of the objects ranged from the surface to an altitude of 99,000 feet.
Further inquiries were suggested to be made directly with the aircrew who made the observations.
sighted object: Various orange-colored objects, a bright light that may have been an explosion, and a bright object that left a yellow trail, exploded, and had a green secondary explosion
location: 188 NM east to 188 NM northeast of Wake Island
